## Step 8: Convert the total energy from Joules to $\mathrm{kcal/mol}$.
First, convert Joules to $\mathrm{kcal}$: $1 \, \mathrm{kcal} = 4184 \, \mathrm{J}$, so $1 \, \mathrm{J} = \frac{1}{4184} \, \mathrm{kcal}$. Thus, $18.7527 \times 10^{-20} \, \mathrm{J} = \frac{18.7527 \times 10^{-20}}{4184} \, \mathrm{kcal} = 4.483 \times 10^{-23} \, \mathrm{kcal}$. To convert to $\mathrm{kcal/mol}$, multiply by Avogadro's number ($6.022 \times 10^{23} \, \mathrm{mol}^{-1}$): $4.483 \times 10^{-23} \times 6.022 \times 10^{23} = 27.0 \, \mathrm{kcal/mol}$.

