## Step 6
Solving for $P(C)$, we get $2P(C) = 1.20 - 0.16 = 1.04$, so $P(C) = 1.04 / 2 = 0.52$.

## Step 7
Now, using $P(T) = P(C) + 0.16$, we find $P(T) = 0.52 + 0.16 = 0.68$.

