The probability of drawing two red balls is $\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{r}{r + 9}$, and the probability of drawing two blue balls is $\frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{r + 9}$. The total probability of drawing two balls of the same color is given by the sum of these probabilities: $\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{r}{r + 9} + \frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{r + 9} = \frac{151}{300}$.

## Step 3: Set up the equation based on the given probability
