## Step 3: Use the given information and the formula for the union of events to express $P(A \cup B)$ and $P\left(A \cup B^{\prime}\right)$.
$P(A \cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B) = 0.76$ and $P\left(A \cup B^{\prime}\right) = P(A) + P\left(B^{\prime}\right) - P\left(A \cap B^{\prime}\right) = 0.87$.

## Step 4: Simplify the expression for $P\left(A \cup B^{\prime}\right)$ using the fact that $P\left(B^{\prime}\right) = 1 - P(B)$ and $P(A) = P(A \cap B) + P\left(A \cap B^{\prime}\right)$.
Since $P(A) = P(A \cap B) + P\left(A \cap B^{\prime}\right)$, we can simplify the given equations. Also, note that $P\left(A \cup B^{\prime}\right) = P(A) + 1 - P(B) - P(A) + P(A \cap B)$, which simplifies to $1 - P(B) + P(A \cap B) = 0.87$.

